# src/parser.c and friends are generated from grammar.js but ARE committed:
# every downstream consumer (nvim-treesitter, Helix, Emacs treesit) compiles
# src/parser.c directly and none of them run `tree-sitter generate`, so leaving
# it out makes the grammar uninstallable without the CLI. CI regenerates and
# fails if the committed copy has drifted - see .github/workflows/ci.yml.
